# Dependencies
node_modules/
.pnpm/
.pnpm-store/

# Build output
dist/
build/
out/
**/target/

# Test / coverage artifacts
coverage/
*.profraw
*.profdata
*.lcov
# Single-file coverage outputs from `go test -coverprofile=` (regenerable)
**/coverage.out
# graphify cache outputs (regenerable; ~200k lines)
graphify-out/
graphify-out/cache/
graphify-out/.graphify_*
graphify-out/graph.html
graphify-out/graph.json
graphify-out/manifest.json
graphify-out/cost.json
# knowledge/ session notes (working memory, not source)
knowledge/

# Probe file used during scaffold-commit testing
_probe_commit_test.txt

# Logs
*.log

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp

# Raw k6 benchmark sample dumps (regenerable; ~82MB each).
# Keep the aggregates: *_summary.json, *_stats.json, *.log, aggregated.json.
*_run[0-9].json
*_run[0-9][0-9].json

# Tool caches
.opencode/tmp/
.opencode/node_modules/
.opencode/package-lock.json

# Agent-platform session state (added 2026-06-21 — see AGENTS.md § "Tooling root convention").
# These folders are produced by editor/CLI tools (OpenCode, Codex, Playwright MCP, omo)
# and should NOT be committed as source. .mavis/ remains the canonical derived view for
# the learner substrate; everything else is platform state.
.omo/boulder.json
.omo/drafts/
.omo/evidence/f3-*.png
.omo/evidence/f3-*.log
.omo/run-continuation/
.codex/napkin.md
.playwright-mcp/console-*.log
.playwright-mcp/page-*.yml
# Allow the curated, human-written evidence files to keep flowing through git:
!.omo/evidence/f*-code-quality.md
!.omo/evidence/f*-scope-fidelity.md
!.omo/evidence/f*-manual-qa.md
!.omo/evidence/task-*.txt
!.omo/notepads/
.mavis/plans/personas-agora-deliverable.tar.gz

# Python bytecode
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# --- Added 2026-06-28 (TECH_DEBT_AUDIT D6/D11): stop committing generated/tool state ---
# Generated graph outputs — only graphify-out/cache/ was ignored before, so the
# rendered report + call-flow HTML leaked into source. They are all derived.
graphify-out/*.html
graphify-out/*.md
graphify-out/*.json
graphify-out/gen_chunk_*.py
# Machine-specific codegraph symlink (absolute path; regenerated per machine).
.codegraph
# One-off committed binary snapshot — regenerate from the live dashboard instead.
codexdojo-dashboard.png
# NOTE: files already committed stay tracked until you run, from the repo root:
#   git rm --cached graphify-out/aidevschool-callflow.html graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md codexdojo-dashboard.png
#   git commit -m "chore: stop tracking generated artifacts (TECH_DEBT_AUDIT D11a)"

# --- Added 2026-07-05 (TECH_DEBT_AUDIT E12): stop committing screenshots ---
# Playwright/design screenshots are regenerable (pnpm run smoke / dev-time captures);
# keep them on disk, out of git. Untracked via `git rm --cached` on the same date.
engines/codexDojo/*.png
engines/codexDojo/shots/
engines/pixelDojo/pixel-quest/shots/

# --- Platform/session state (per AGENTS.md): never commit tool/machine state ---
.commandcode/
.compozy/agents/
.omo/
.serena/
.opencode/
.playwright-mcp/
.codex/
.notebook/
.zcode/

# Playwright test-results artifacts (regenerable: produced by `pnpm run smoke`).
**/test-results/

# --- Added 2026-07-08 (docs/TECH_DEBT_AUDIT_2026-07-08.md, items 2-3) ---
# Smoke screenshots are regenerable; evidence files (evidence.json/.ndjson,
# live-evidence*) stay tracked — they are the learning-gate audit trail.
engines/voxelDojo/game-*/.logs/*.png
engines/pixelDojo/games/*/shots/*.png
# Compiled Go binaries (build output; rebuild with `go build`).
curriculum/02_key_value_store/go-impl/kvstore
curriculum/07_rest_api_auth/go-impl/server
curriculum/08_event_driven_order_system/go-impl/event-driven-order-go
curriculum/09_plugin_system/go-impl/plugin-system-go

